.TH "emac_dev_tx_timeout" 9 "emac_dev_tx_timeout" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
emac_dev_tx_timeout \- EMAC Transmit timeout function
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" emac_dev_tx_timeout
.BI "(struct net_device *ndev "  ","
.BI "unsigned int txqueue "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ndev" 12
The DaVinci EMAC network adapter
.IP "txqueue" 12
the index of the hung transmit queue
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Called when system detects that a skb timeout period has expired
potentially due to a fault in the adapter in not being able to send
it out on the wire. We teardown the TX channel assuming a hardware
error and re-initialize the TX channel for hardware operation
